You could look in 'Contemporary Cryptology', there the iterated knpsack
and how to break it are explained. And there are some pointers to the
original papers wich might help you...
Contemporary Cryptology - The science of information integrity
(c)1992 IEEE Press NY. OrderNo PC0271-7 ISBN:0-87942-277-7
Or you might look for pointers in:
E.F.Brickwell "Breaking iterated knpasacks" Procedings of Crypto'84
(vol.12 pp 342-358)

Good luck,
    /gec


